#. Plugin Name of the plugin
#: solvebeam-boilerplate.php
msgid "SolveBeam Default Customer Location for WooCommerce"
msgstr "SolveBeam Default Customer Location for WooCommerce"

#. Plugin URI of the plugin
#. Author URI of the plugin
#: solvebeam-boilerplate.php
msgid "https://www.solvebeam.com/"
msgstr "https://www.solvebeam.com/"

#. Description of the plugin
#: solvebeam-boilerplate.php
msgid ""
"Override the default customer location used by WooCommerce for taxes, "
"pricing, and checkout."
msgstr ""
"Overschrijf de standaard klantlocatie die WooCommerce gebruikt voor "
"belastingen, prijzen en afrekenen."

#. Author of the plugin
#: solvebeam-boilerplate.php
msgid "SolveBeam"
msgstr "SolveBeam"

#: psr-4/Plugin.php:79
msgid "Settings"
msgstr "Instellingen"

#: psr-4/Plugin.php:127
msgid "Override shop country/region for customer location"
msgstr "Standaard winkel-land/regio overschrijven voor klantlocatie"

#: psr-4/Plugin.php:128
msgid ""
"Use this setting when the 'Default customer location' above is set to 'Shop "
"country/region', but you want to set a different default location for "
"customers. For example, if your store is based in the Netherlands, but you "
"primarily sell to customers in Germany, select 'Germany' here. New visitors "
"will then immediately see prices and shipping options applicable to Germany."
msgstr ""
"Gebruik deze instelling wanneer “Standaard klantlocatie” hierboven is "
"ingesteld op “Winkel-land/regio”, maar je een andere standaardlocatie voor "
"klanten wilt instellen. Als je winkel bijvoorbeeld is gevestigd in "
"Nederland, maar je voornamelijk aan klanten in Duitsland verkoopt, selecteer "
"je hier “Duitsland”. Nieuwe bezoekers zien dan direct prijzen en "
"verzendopties die van toepassing zijn op Duitsland."

#: psr-4/Plugin.php:129
msgid ""
"This setting is added by the <i>SolveBeam Default Customer Location for "
"WooCommerce</i> plugin."
msgstr ""
"Deze instelling wordt toegevoegd door de plugin <i>SolveBeam Default "
"Customer Location for WooCommerce</i>."
